content=["<dl>",
"<dt><a href='#Section0'>Peptic ulcer disease</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section0'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Evidence of GI bleeding, weight loss, early satiety, a palpable mass or lymphadenopathy, jaundice, progressive dysphagia, recurrent vomiting, FHx of cancer, or onset of symptoms after age 55 increases the likelihood of cancer. [26]",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Distinguished from gastric neoplasm by endoscopy and biopsy. All peptic ulcers should have repeat endoscopy after treatment to document healing.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section1'>Benign oesophageal stricture</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section1'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> May have a hx of gastro-oesophageal reflux disease.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Distinguished from gastric neoplasm by endoscopy and biopsy.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section2'>Achalasia</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section2'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Suspect malignancy in patients with symptoms for &lt;6 months, presentation after age 60, and excessive weight loss relative to the duration of symptoms. [27]",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Distinguished from gastric neoplasm by manometry, endoscopy, and biopsy.Pseudoachalasia is the term for features of achalasia (based on barium esophagography, managraphy, and endoscopy findings) that are ultimately shown to be due to malignancy.</p>",
"</dd>",
"</dl>"].join("\n");